g and outsourcing services revenue us billion  operating income us billion  profit us billion  total assets us billion  total equity us billion  number of employees   q website wwwcognizantcom cognizant is an american multinational corporation that provides digital technology consulting and operations services it is headquartered in teaneck new jersey united states cognizant is listed in the nasdaq and the sp  indices it was founded as an inhouse technology unit of dun  bradstreet in  and started serving external clients in  it made an initial public offering in  after a series of corporate splits and restructures of its parent companies it was the first software services firm listed on the nasdaq during the dot com bust it grew by accepting the application maintenance work that the bigger players were unwilling to perform gradually it ventured into application development complex systems integration and consulting work cognizant had a period of fast growth during the s becoming a fortune  company in  in  the fortune magazine named it as the worlds fourth most admired it services company contents  history  acquisitions  services  business model  outsourcing controversy and hiring in the us  operations  regions  business units  corporate affairs  marketing and branding  finance  corporate social responsibility  environmental record  fortune   others  see also  references  external links historyedit cognizant began as dun  bradstreet satyam software dbss established as dun  bradstreets inhouse technology unit focused on implementing largescale it projects for dun  bradstreet businesses in  the company started pursuing customers beyond dun  bradstreet in  dun  bradstreet spun off several of its subsidiaries including erisco ims international nielsen media research pilot software strategic technologies and dbss to form a new company called cognizant corporation three months later in  dbss renamed itself to cognizant technology solutions in july  dun  bradstreet bought satyams  stake in dbss for  million headquarters were moved to the united states and in march  kumar mahadeva was named ceo operating as a division of the cognizant corporation the company mainly focused on ykrelated projects and web development in  the parent company cognizant corporation split into two companies ims health and nielsen media research after this restructuring cognizant technology solutions became a public subsidiary of ims health in june  ims health partially spun off the company conducting an initial public offering of the cognizant stock the company raised  million less than what the ims health underwriters had hoped for they earmarked the money for debt payments and upgrading company offices kumar mahadeva decided to reduce the companys dependence on yk projects by q   of companys revenues came from yk projects compared with  in early  believing that the  billion enterprise resource planning software market was saturated mahadeva decided to refrain from largescale erp implementation projects instead he focused on applications management which accounted for  of cognizants revenue in q  cognizants revenues in  were  million and the company had zero debt with  million in the bank during the dotcom bust the company grew by taking on the maintenance projects that larger it services companies did not want in  ims health sold its entire  stake in cognizant which instituted a poison pill provision to prevent hostile takeover attempts kumar mahadeva resigned as the ceo in  and was replaced by lakshmi narayanan gradually the companys services portfolio expanded across the it services landscape and into business process outsourcing bpo and business consulting lakshmi narayanan was succeeded by the kenyaborn francisco dsouza in  cognizant experienced a period of fast growth during the s as reflected by its appearance in fortune magazines  fastestgrowing companies list for ten consecutive years from  to  in september  cognizant struck its biggest deal acquiring healthcare it services provider trizetto corp for  billion cognizant shares rose nearly  percent in premarket trading acquisitionsedit company acquired country date business reference tmg health usa june  health care it  brilliantservice japan march  intelligent products internet of things  adaptra australia december  insurance consulting project management  nova it australia december  hr services   kis information services kis germany december  it services  mirabeau bv netherlands november  digital marketing customer experience  frontica business solutions norway october  it services  solutions  idea couture canada july  digital services innovation and experience design  heliocentric el salvador may  bpo services  quick left inc usa may  mobile  web apps  red associates denmark april  human sciences  kbace technologies usa january  oracle cloud erp  storebrand baltic lithuania nov  lithuanian it unit of norway’s storebrand  cno financial group india india feb  it application development  odecee australia november  it consulting and bpo services  cadient group usa october  digital healthcare  trizetto corp usa september  healthcare payer software provider revenue cycle software consulting software bpo hosting  itaas interactive tv solutions usa april  digital video services  valuesource technologies india october  it services  equinox consulting france october  financial services consulting firm  sourcenet solutions usa may  bps for finance  accounting  c group  companies germany december  btconsult gbbb process and technology consulting sap c solutions gmbh consulting and enterprise solutions sap bpm ecm erm psc management consulting gmbh process and technology consulting c setcon gmbh software engineering and testing enterprise services ag a swiss company focused on process and it consulting c holding gmbh  medicall philippines november  medical transcription  excellence data research india august  market research  ing us usa june  technology  zaffera usa september  sap consulting  corelogic india india july  mortgage processing  galileo performance france june  consulting related to the measurement management and continuous optimization of it system performance  pipc group uk may  program  project management consulting  ubs india service center india october  business process outsourcing industry research  pepperweed advisors us  september  business consulting program management  invensys rail rd india  invensys operations managed rd center india india july  product research  engineering manufacturing  active intelligence canada february  consulting implementation and support services for oracle retail merchandising planning and optimization suite  strategic vision consulting us june  business consulting for media and entertainment companies  tsystems india germany march  system integration  marketrx us  november  life sciences analytics healthcare kpo  aimnet us september  it infrastructure services  fathom consulting canada april  telecom  automotive it services  ygyan consulting india february  sap consulting  infopulse netherlands december  it services  aces international us april  siebel crm consulting  american express travelrelated services account from silverline technologies us sep  financial services  unitedhealthcare ireland limited ireland june  healthcare services a subsidiary of the unitedhealth group  servicesedit cognizant provides information technology information security consulting ito and bpo services these include business  technology consulting systems integration application development  maintenance it infrastructure services analytics business intelligence data warehousing customer relationship management supply chain management engineering  manufacturing solutions enterprise resource planning research and development outsourcing and testing solutions cognizant digital works — created to help clients rapidly build pilot and scale enterpriselevel digital initiatives — is central to cognizants efforts to help clients drive business change across their operations and inform their gotomarket activities business modeledit cognizants original corporate headquarters in chennai now an offshore delivery center like many other it services firms cognizant follows a global delivery model based on offshore software rd and offshore outsourcing the company has a number of offshore development centers outside the united states and nearshore centers in the us europe and south america in its early years cognizant gained business from a number of american and european companies with the help of the dun  bradstreet brand the companys senior executives envisaged the firm as a provider of highend customer services onpar with the six contemporary major system integrators accenture bearingpoint capgemini ey deloitte and ibm but at lower prices outsourcing controversy and hiring in the usedit cognizant is number one in top  companies receiving hb visas to bring immigrant workers to the united states the company has been steadily increasing its us work force in january  the company announced plans to expand its us delivery centers including a new person facility in phoenix arizona in february  cognizant said it had  fulltime recruiters actively hiring in the us in  an investigation by the us department of labor dol found cognizant in violation of the hb provisions of the immigration and nationality administrative act dol found that  of its workers hired under the hb program were underpaid according to cognizant this was due to unintentional administrative errors the dol investigation revealed that cognizant had achieved  compliance in its management of hb visarelated issues the company paid us in back wages to the  employees no fines or visa restrictions were imposed since dol did not discover any willful violations joseph petrecca the director of the wage and hour divisions northern new jersey district office praised the company for taking immediate steps to correct the violations this level of cooperation sets a standard for others in the industry in  the company was the subject of a lawsuit by workers for walt disney world who said workers from india were brought into the united states on hb visas in order to replace them however in october  federal judge gregory a presnel of the united states district court in orlando has dismissed the lawsuits stating none of the allegedly false statements put at issue in the complaint are adequate operationsedit regionsedit in addition to its global headquarters and delivery center in teaneck new jersey and the us headquarters in college station texas cognizant has  other us delivery centers bentonville arkansas bridgewater new jersey des moines iowa holliston massachusetts minot north dakota phoenix arizona southfield michigan williston vermont st louis missouri union new jersey sacramento california charlotte north carolina oklahoma city oklahoma washington pennsylvania malvern pennsylvania naperville illinois carmel indiana linthicum maryland and tampa florida the company has more than  employees globally of which over  are in india across  locations with a plurality in chennai the other centers of the company are in bangalore coimbatore gurgaon noida hyderabad kochi kolkata mangalore mumbai and pune the company has local regional and global delivery centers in the uk hungary the netherlands spain china philippines canada brazil argentina mexico etc business unitsedit cognizant is organized into several verticals and horizontal units the vertical units focus on specific industries such as banking  financial services healthcare manufacturing and retail the horizontals focus on specific technologies or process areas such as analytics mobile computing bpo and testing both horizontal and vertical units have business consultants who together form the organizationwide cognizant business consulting cbc team cognizant is among the largest recruiters of mbas in the industry they are involved in business development and business analysis for it services projects according to the  financial statements the major portion of cognizants revenues is derived from clients in the financial services  and healthcare  industries other substantial revenue sources include clients from manufacturing retail  logistics  and communications information media  entertainment and technology  industries by geography most of the revenue is derived from north america  and europe  corporate affairsedit marketing and brandingedit the companys flagship customer conference is cognizant community it is held annually in the united states europe australia and asia singapore india and japan the summit which features notable keynote speakers in the world of business technology economics and even adventure sports has been praised as a model industry event financeedit cognizant was listed on nasdaq in  and added to the nasdaq index in  after the close of trading on  november  cognizant moved from the mid cap sp  to the sp  the company claims it is in excellent financial health reporting over  billion in cash and short term investments for the quarter ending  september  net income for  was  billion as against  billion in  and  percent up in the fourth quarter to  million corporate social responsibilityedit cognizants philanthropic and corporate social responsibility csr initiatives are conducted through the cognizant employees for the financial and administrative support of the cognizant foundation registered in march  as a charitable company under the indian companies act the cognizant foundation aims to help unprivileged members of society gain access to quality education and healthcare by providing financial and technical support designing and implementing educational and healthcare improvement programs and partnering with nongovernment organizations ngos educational institutions healthcare institutions government agencies and corporations cognizant has a grassroots corporate social responsibility project called outreach for which cognizants employees volunteer to support schools and orphanages at the  maker faire the company announced plans to fund a maker space at the new york hall of science a making the future afterschool program and a partnership with citizen schools to promote stem education in the united states in  cognizant foundation made donation to vidnyanvahini a notforprofit organization located in pune in india for its mobile science laboratory msl environmental recordedit cognizants sustainability efforts include a go green initiative launched in  focused on energy conservation recycling and responsible waste management in october  newsweek magazine ranked cognizant th among the  largest publicly traded companies in america in its annual green rankings fortune edit year rank               othersedit on  june  the company signed a multimilliondollar agreement with escorts group in india to help escorts businesses in digital transformation and modernizing its operations across all business segments on  june  it partnered with singaporebased supermarket retailer ntuc fairprice to perform digital transformation in ntucs business to improve personalized and consistent customer service across multiple channels see alsoedit companies portal disney litigation francisco dsouza kumar mahadeva lakshmi narayanan srini raju tech companies in the new york city metropolitan region referencesedit  a b c d e  sec filing sec   cognizant technology solutions corporation ctsh seeking alpha retrieved may     a b c mishra pankaj  cognizant’s francisco d’souza the horizon chasers live mint and the wall street journal  march  retrieved on  from httpwwwlivemintcomcompaniesvduuoufvotxrmyarjjijcognizantsfranciscodsouzathehorizonchaserhtml  cognizant joins the fortune  club rediff  may  retrieved  june    worlds most admired companies information technology services  fortune retrieved  july    cognizant is like a billion tech startup retrieved    dun  bradstreet satyam to be rech