nuary   founder kumar mahadeva headquarters teaneck new jersey united states area served worldwide key people francisco dsouza ceo lakshmi narayanan vicechairman services it services business consulting and outsourcing services revenue us billion  operating income us billion  profit us billion  total assets us billion  total equity us billion  number of employees   q website wwwcognizantcom cognizant is an american multinational corporation that provides digital technology consulting and operations services it is headquartered in teaneck new jersey united states cognizant is listed in the nasdaq and the sp  indices it was founded as an inhouse technology unit of dun  bradstreet in  and started serving external clients in  it made an initial public offering in  after a series of corporate splits and restructures of its parent companies it was the first software services firm listed on the nasdaq during the dot com bust it grew by accepting the application maintenance work that the bigger players were unwilling to perform gradually it ventured into application development complex systems integration and consulting work cognizant had a period of fast growth during the s becoming a fortune  company in  in  the fortune magazine named it as the worlds fourth most admired it services company contents  history  acquisitions  services  business model  outsourcing controversy and hiring in the us  operations  regions  business units  corporate affairs  marketing and branding  finance  corporate social responsibility  environmental record  fortune   others  see also  references  external links historyedit cognizant began as dun  bradstreet satyam software dbss established as dun  bradstreets inhouse technology unit focused on implementing largescale it projects for dun  bradstreet businesses in  the company started pursuing customers beyond dun  bradstreet in  dun  bradstreet spun off several of its subsidiaries including erisco ims international nielsen media research pilot software strategic technologies and dbss to form a new company called cognizant corporation three months later in  dbss renamed itself to cognizant technology solutions in july  dun  bradstreet bought satyams  stake in dbss for  million headquarters were moved to the united states and in march  kumar mahadeva was named ceo operating as a division of the cognizant corporation the company mainly focused on ykrelated projects and web development in  the parent company cognizant corporation split into two companies ims health and nielsen media research after this restructuring cognizant technology solutions became a public subsidiary of ims health in june  ims health partially spun off the company conducting an initial public offering of the cognizant stock the company raised  million less than what the ims health underwriters had hoped for they earmarked the money for debt payments and upgrading company offices kumar mahadeva decided to reduce the companys dependence on yk projects by q   of companys revenues came from yk projects compared with  in early  believing that the  billion enterprise resource planning software market was saturated mahadeva decided to refrain from largescale erp implementation projects instead he focused on applications management which accounted for  of cognizants revenue in q  cognizants revenues in  were  million and the company had zero debt with  million in the bank during the dotcom bust the company grew by taking on the maintenance projects that larger it services companies did not want in  ims health sold its entire  stake in cognizant which instituted a poison pill provision to prevent hostile takeover attempts kumar mahadeva resigned as the ceo in  and was replaced by lakshmi narayanan gradually the companys services portfolio expanded across the it services landscape and into business process outsourcing bpo and business consulting lakshmi narayanan was succeeded by the kenyaborn francisco dsouza in  cognizant experienced a period of fast growth during the s as reflected by its appearance in fortune magazines  fastestgrowing companies list for ten consecutive years from  to  in september  cognizant struck its biggest deal acquiring healthcare it services provider trizetto corp for  billion cognizant shares rose nearly  percent in premarket trading acquisitionsedit company acquired country date business reference tmg health usa june  health care it  brilliantservice japan march  intelligent products internet of things  adaptra australia december  insurance consulting project management  nova it australia december  hr services   kis information services kis germany december  it services  mirabeau bv netherlands november  digital marketing customer experience  frontica business solutions norway october  it services  solutions  idea couture canada july  digital services innovation and experience design  heliocentric el salvador may  bpo services  quick left inc usa may  mobile  web apps  red associates denmark april  human sciences  kbace technologies usa january  oracle cloud erp  storebrand baltic lithuania nov  lithuanian it unit of norway’s storebrand  cno financial group india india feb  it application development  odecee australia november  it consulting and bpo services  cadient group usa october  digital healthcare  trizetto corp usa september  healthcare payer software provider revenue cycle software consulting software bpo hosting  itaas interactive tv solutions usa april  digital video services  valuesource technologies india october  it services  equinox consulting france october  financial services consulting firm  sourcenet solutions usa may  bps for finance  accounting  c group  companies germany december  btconsult gbbb process and technology consulting sap c solutions gmbh consulting and enterprise solutions sap bpm ecm erm psc management consulting gmbh process and technology consulting c setcon gmbh software engineering and testing enterprise services ag a swiss company focused o